article.headline: Belmont 77, Stetson 58
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Adam Mark had 31 points and 11 rebounds, both season highs, as Belmont won its fifth straight at home, 77-58 over Stetson on Monday night. Stetson (2-7, 0-3 Atlantic Sun Conference) held a 4-2 lead in the opening minutes. But Belmont (8-3, 3-1) went on a 25-4 run midway through the first half to take a 32-10 advantage capped by Mark's 3-point play with 8:17 left. The Hatters' E.J. Gordon scored just 7 points on 3-of-11 shooting with four turnovers forced by the defensive tandem Jese Snyder and Josh Goodwin. He had entered the game as the conference's leading scorer, averaging 20.4 points and had scored in double figures in 23 straight games. Goodwin finished with 12 points and Brian Collins added 11 for the Bruins. Anthony Register scored 17 points and Mark Stiles had 11 for Stetson.
